with a magnifying glass!

01:27:07.595 --> 01:27:10.955
It was quite simply
the worst night of my life.

01:27:10.995 --> 01:27:12.875
My embarrassment
compounded by the fact

01:27:12.915 --> 01:27:14.755
that Victor
had now slept with

01:27:14.795 --> 01:27:19.115
2 out of the 3 members
of my family.

01:28:00.355 --> 01:28:02.275
Jennifer, I was just
gonna pick you up.

01:28:02.275 --> 01:28:03.955
I got a ride.
Iorenzo drove me.

01:28:03.995 --> 01:28:05.635
You all right?
How do you feel?

01:28:05.635 --> 01:28:07.035
Fine.

01:28:07.075 --> 01:28:08.955
Where'd you meet
lorenzo?

01:28:08.995 --> 01:28:10.915
At the hospital.
Iorenzo!

01:28:10.955 --> 01:28:12.595
He took
wonderful care of me.

01:28:12.635 --> 01:28:14.155
He's studying
to be a doctor.

01:28:14.195 --> 01:28:15.675
I want you
to meet my father.

01:28:15.715 --> 01:28:17.555
Oh.

01:28:17.595 --> 01:28:19.515
It's a great
pleasure, sir.

01:28:19.555 --> 01:28:22.755
Him.

01:28:22.795 --> 01:28:24.235
Get your stuff.
We're going.

01:28:24.275 --> 01:28:25.675
That's what
I wanted to ask you.

01:28:25.675 --> 01:28:26.475
What?

01:28:26.515 --> 01:28:27.715
Can I stay?

01:28:27.755 --> 01:28:28.875
Stay where?

01:28:28.915 --> 01:28:32.275
Here. We still have
the house for another week.

01:28:32.315 --> 01:28:34.395
Nicky'll stay with me,
wouldn't you?

01:28:34.435 --> 01:28:35.795
Could I?

01:28:35.835 --> 01:28:37.755
Are you staying?

01:28:37.795 --> 01:28:38.195
No.

01:28:38.235 --> 01:28:40.115
Then you can stay.

01:28:40.155 --> 01:28:41.555
You don't mind
leaving them alone?

01:28:41.595 --> 01:28:43.995
You mean they might not
behave as well as we did?

01:28:43.995 --> 01:28:45.435
Lorenzo will
look out for us.

01:28:45.435 --> 01:28:47.795
He said he would.

01:28:47.795 --> 01:28:50.315
What the hell do I know
about lorenzo?

01:28:50.355 --> 01:28:51.715
He's 21.

01:28:51.755 --> 01:28:54.115
He's perfect.
I love him.

01:28:54.155 --> 01:28:57.035
Ok, I better go call
the airlines and tell them.

01:28:57.035 --> 01:28:58.715
Victor!

01:28:58.755 --> 01:29:01.635
Come see the house.
It's beautiful. Nicky?

01:29:01.675 --> 01:29:04.075
It all worked out
very neatly...

01:29:04.115 --> 01:29:06.475
except for me,
the odd man out.

01:29:06.515 --> 01:29:09.635
Well, no complaints.
I made my own bed.

01:29:09.675 --> 01:29:15.915
I just never thought
I'd wind up in it alone.

01:29:15.955 --> 01:29:18.715
Uncle Matthew,
you were right, you know.

01:29:18.715 --> 01:29:21.555
I can't imagine
about what.

01:29:21.555 --> 01:29:24.435
That was a dream
I had on the beach

01:29:24.475 --> 01:29:28.275
a beautiful dream.

01:29:33.075 --> 01:29:36.435
Will you forget me

01:29:36.475 --> 01:29:39.795
the minute I die.

01:29:48.235 --> 01:29:49.715
I'm serious.
I don't know when.

01:29:49.755 --> 01:29:52.715
Your own divorce and
you don't know when?

01:29:52.755 --> 01:29:55.235
I can get it tomorrow if I want
to cave in to her lawyers.

01:29:55.275 --> 01:29:57.355
Otherwise,
it's gonna take months.

01:29:57.395 --> 01:29:59.715
Months?

01:29:59.755 --> 01:30:02.315
At least.

01:30:02.355 --> 01:30:04.875
And then?

01:30:04.915 --> 01:30:06.355
It'll be over.
I'll be free.

01:30:06.395 --> 01:30:08.715
Mmm.

01:30:08.755 --> 01:30:12.115
Just about the time
I could be.

01:30:12.155 --> 01:30:13.035
Yeah.

01:30:13.075 --> 01:30:14.475
Careful, Victor.

01:30:14.515 --> 01:30:17.155
Don't let your enthusiasm
run away with you.

01:30:17.195 --> 01:30:19.795
Karen, we don't want
to rush into anything.

01:30:19.835 --> 01:30:22.635
Not a second time,
certainly.

01:30:22.675 --> 01:30:26.675
Don't panic, Victor,
I have no demands.

01:30:26.715 --> 01:30:30.715
We helped each other
through a bad time.

01:30:30.915 --> 01:30:32.595
Can I still see you?

01:30:32.635 --> 01:30:34.075
I don't think so, Victor.

01:30:34.115 --> 01:30:35.955
Why not?

01:30:35.995 --> 01:30:38.315
Your fly is open.

01:30:38.315 --> 01:30:39.715
Not now.

01:30:39.715 --> 01:30:44.035
Just most of the time.

01:30:51.915 --> 01:30:54.315
You going to Sao Paulo

01:30:54.355 --> 01:30:55.715
I guess.

01:30:55.755 --> 01:30:57.675
I'm going to bahía

01:30:57.715 --> 01:30:59.555
it figures.

01:30:59.595 --> 01:31:02.475
My hotel room's
paid for the month.

01:31:02.515 --> 01:31:05.635
Right.
What's Victor up to?

01:31:05.675 --> 01:31:07.435
He's packing.

01:31:07.475 --> 01:31:10.395
Mm-hmm.

01:31:10.435 --> 01:31:14.835
Have you got room
in your bag for these?

01:31:14.875 --> 01:31:16.075
Don't you want them
in bahía?

01:31:16.115 --> 01:31:18.275
They're going to bahía.

01:31:18.275 --> 01:31:22.235
I don't understand.

01:31:22.235 --> 01:31:26.115
You're going to bahía.

01:31:26.155 --> 01:31:28.555
We've got a lot
to talk about, Matthew.

01:31:28.595 --> 01:31:29.755
Do you want to talk?

01:31:29.795 --> 01:31:31.715
You think I want
to throw 20 years away

01:31:31.755 --> 01:31:34.115
just because of
your foolishness?

01:31:34.155 --> 01:31:35.475
Or mine?

01:31:35.515 --> 01:31:36.755
Karen-

01:31:36.795 --> 01:31:39.635
it's going to be
a long haul, Matthew.

01:31:39.675 --> 01:31:42.075
There's an awful lot
for both of us to forget.

01:31:42.115 --> 01:31:44.275
Let alone forgive.

01:31:44.315 --> 01:31:45.395
Mm-hmm.

01:31:45.435 --> 01:31:47.595
No more "mmms," Matthew.

01:31:47.635 --> 01:31:49.395
I want you to talk to me.

01:31:49.435 --> 01:31:51.155
Reach down
in your feelings

01:31:51.195 --> 01:31:53.115
and tell me what
you're thinking,

01:31:53.115 --> 01:31:54.035
what you're afraid of.

01:31:54.075 --> 01:31:57.115
I want you to stop
bottling it all up.

01:31:57.155 --> 01:31:58.035
I'll do my best.

01:31:58.075 --> 01:32:01.435
I'll take your worst, too.
Just share with me.

01:32:01.475 --> 01:32:05.955
I'll do my worst.

01:32:05.995 --> 01:32:10.475
We better hurry.

01:32:13.035 --> 01:32:17.155
Victor... wait.

01:32:17.195 --> 01:32:20.395
Come on.

01:32:20.435 --> 01:32:21.835
I'm so glad we got to stay.

01:32:21.875 --> 01:32:24.275
They're coming.
I'm gonna talk to my mom.

01:32:24.315 --> 01:32:25.955
What's happening?

01:32:25.995 --> 01:32:27.595
We're leaving.

01:32:27.635 --> 01:32:30.995
You and mom,
as in together?

01:32:31.035 --> 01:32:34.355
We'll be at club med
in bahía.

01:32:41.035 --> 01:32:42.955
Goodbye, Jennifer.

01:32:42.955 --> 01:32:46.795
Goodbye,
uncle Matthew.

01:32:51.715 --> 01:32:55.995
Nicky, uh...

01:32:56.035 --> 01:33:00.315
I love you, too.

01:33:00.315 --> 01:33:01.755
We've got a lot
to talk about.

01:33:01.795 --> 01:33:03.635
I know.

01:33:03.675 --> 01:33:06.035
I'm so glad
you're leaving

01:33:06.075 --> 01:33:09.915
I'll see you back
in Sao Paulo.

01:33:16.155 --> 01:33:17.595
Goodbye, uncle Victor.

01:33:17.635 --> 01:33:18.515
Goodbye, nick.

01:33:18.555 --> 01:33:21.435
And thanks
for whatever you did.

01:33:21.475 --> 01:33:23.315
I didn't do anything.

01:33:23.355 --> 01:33:29.595
Thank god
somebody didn't.

01:33:29.595 --> 01:33:30.715
Goodbye,
aunt Karen

01:33:30.715 --> 01:33:33.115
goodbye, Jennifer.
Take care of yourself.

01:33:33.155 --> 01:33:36.195
Try not to play
with anything sharp.

01:33:36.235 --> 01:33:39.555
We gotta move.

01:33:42.715 --> 01:33:43.675
What's that?

01:33:43.715 --> 01:33:44.595
Sunglasses.

01:33:44.635 --> 01:33:46.315
The other thing.

01:33:46.355 --> 01:33:47.995
Uh, I-I don't know.

01:33:48.035 --> 01:33:49.395
Nothing.

01:33:49.435 --> 01:33:53.275
And I've heard
all I want out of you.

01:33:53.355 --> 01:33:56.035
Go.

01:33:56.035 --> 01:33:58.035
Terrific.
I wind up being your driver.

01:33:58.075 --> 01:34:00.475
I hope you're better at
that than being a friend.

01:34:00.515 --> 01:34:01.875
You're kidding.
After what you've done

01:34:01.915 --> 01:34:03.835
I don't know how you can
look me in the face.

01:34:03.835 --> 01:34:04.755
Which one, Victor?

01:34:04.795 --> 01:34:06.315
Which face did you
have in mind?

01:34:06.355 --> 01:34:07.235
It's hard to realize

01:34:07.275 --> 01:34:09.675
a whole year has
gone by since then.

01:34:09.715 --> 01:34:11.595
Victor finally
got his divorce,

01:34:11.635 --> 01:34:13.515
then he and his wife
turned around

01:34:13.555 --> 01:34:14.915
and married
each other again.

01:34:14.955 --> 01:34:17.355
Victor said it's because
she wanted to get

01:34:17.355 --> 01:34:19.755
the other half
of everything he owned.

01:34:19.755 --> 01:34:21.155
With Karen and me,

01:34:21.195 --> 01:34:23.555
it wasn't really a case
of happily ever after.

01:34:23.555 --> 01:34:27.035
We were lucky to get any kind
of ever after at all.

01:34:27.075 --> 01:34:30.755
I figure we're a few months
away from happily.

01:34:30.795 --> 01:34:31.995
But we'll make it.

01:34:32.035 --> 01:34:33.115
You only live once,

01:34:33.155 --> 01:34:35.555
but it does help if you
get to be young twice.

01:34:35.595 --> 01:34:38.395
